Ms. Luo.

44
00:03:48,700 --> 00:03:51,700
I told you to drive. Just do it.

45
00:04:11,400 --> 00:04:13,600
<i>[Gu Yi Chen: No more work allowed.]</i>

46
00:04:16,600 --> 00:04:20,200
<i>[What can I do? The boss is pressing me.]</i>

47
00:04:20,200 --> 00:04:22,000
<i>[Fire your boss.]</i>

48
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:24,300
<i>[Really?]</i>

49
00:04:24,300 --> 00:04:26,900
<i>[Starting tomorrow, you can support me.]</i>

50
00:04:27,600 --> 00:04:30,600
<i>[Get some rest early, Producer Zhao.]</i>

51
00:04:31,800 --> 00:04:35,400
<i>[Got it, my great Mr. Gu.]</i>

52
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:43,500
There's still so much left to be drawn.

53
00:04:53,800 --> 00:04:55,200
<i>Congratulations, Yi Chen.</i>

54
00:04:55,200 --> 00:04:58,500
<i>Your letter confirmed that the occurrence of a special allergy</i>

55
00:04:58,500 --> 00:05:02,000
<i>is deeply connected to feelings and emotions.</i>

56
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:05,000
<i>Your love has greatly reduced your allergies.</i>

57
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:09,700
<i>Your lover also gives you a sense of emotional stability.</i>

58
00:05:09,700 --> 00:05:11,800
<i>I should also congratulate you.</i>

59
00:05:11,800 --> 00:05:15,300
<i>Maybe it's almost time you got over psychogenic allergies,</i>

60
00:05:15,300 --> 00:05:20,300
<i>and the girl you love deeply, and who loves you deeply, may truly be your destiny.</i>

61
00:05:20,300 --> 00:05:22,200
<i>I wish you happiness.</i>

62
00:05:36,700 --> 00:05:40,200
Perhaps, it really takes a lifetime of good luck

63
00:05:40,200 --> 00:05:45,400
to exchange for the destined encounter with you.

64
00:05:54,600 --> 00:05:56,100
It's too late.

65
00:05:56,100 --> 00:05:57,600
Why am I like Nuan Nuan now?

66
00:05:57,600 --> 00:06:00,300
I didn't even hear the alarm clock.

67
00:06:00,300 --> 00:06:03,800
It's not that you didn't hear the alarm. Zhao Nuan Nuan left half an hour ago.

68
00:06:03,800 --> 00:06:05,900
Nuan Nuan left so early?

69
00:06:05,900 --> 00:06:08,400
She was promoted to producer. She is really different now.

70
00:06:08,400 --> 00:06:11,000
All right, it's my fault.

71
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:13,500
It seems I have to rely on myself to get up early in the future.

72
00:06:13,500 --> 00:06:17,000
Wait, wait. You haven't had breakfast yet.

73
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:18,800
I'm not eating.

74
00:06:18,800 --> 00:06:20,800
Wait, wait.

75
00:06:21,800 --> 00:06:25,100
Your lipstick is uneven, and you're going to work like this?

76
00:06:31,200 --> 00:06:33,200
I'm making more and more mistakes.

77
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:36,500
Mirror!

78
00:06:39,100 --> 00:06:41,000
I am your mirror.

79
00:07:40,300 --> 00:07:43,900
Where's my notebook? How did I forget it again?

80
00:07:45,300 --> 00:07:47,200
What's the matter with you?

81
00:07:48,400 --> 00:07:50,600
What's that expression for?

82
00:07:53,200 --> 00:07:58,200
I... I… What expression?

83
00:07:59,600 --> 00:08:02,800
That's clearly a guilty expression.

84
00:08:04,800 --> 00:08:06,500
Zhao Ming Yang,

85
00:08:06,500 --> 00:08:10,400
are you doing something bad behind my back?

86
00:08:10,400 --> 00:08:12,000
No, not at all.

87
00:08:19,400 --> 00:08:21,300
Are you still denying it?

88
00:08:21,300 --> 00:08:23,800
Since we were small, you look away when you lie.

89
00:08:23,800 --> 00:08:25,400
You are like that now.

90
00:08:25,400 --> 00:08:28,800
No, no, I'm not.

91
00:08:30,600 --> 00:08:32,600
What are you hiding?

92
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:36,000
What's wrong with the couch?

93
00:08:39,200 --> 00:08:41,300
Behind the couch…

94
00:08:41,300 --> 00:08:43,500
Is someone there?

95
00:08:43,500 --> 00:08:45,200
No, there isn't!

96
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:48,900
There's no one behind the couch.

97
00:09:06,600 --> 00:09:08,400
No one?

98
00:09:10,800 --> 00:09:13,800
Then why did you set two breakfasts?

99
00:09:13,800 --> 00:09:16,500
Also, two pairs of chopsticks.

100
00:09:17,600 --> 00:09:19,000
Is Big Sister Xin Ran still at home?

101
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:21,400
No, it's just me.

102
00:09:23,200 --> 00:09:26,800
You… Didn't you return for your notebook?

103
00:09:27,800 --> 00:09:31,100
Right, I came for my notebook.

104
00:09:35,700 --> 00:09:38,900
Xin Ran, hurry up. It's not safe here.

105
00:09:54,600 --> 00:09:56,800
Did you hear noise on the balcony?

106
00:09:57,600 --> 00:09:59,600
Is someone still in the house?

107
00:09:59,600 --> 00:10:02,000
No, there isn't.

108
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:05,200
I remember! It's the neighbor's cat.

109
00:10:05,200 --> 00:10:08,400
The next door lady's cat is extremely timid.

110
00:10:15,800 --> 00:10:17,300
Is that right?

111
00:10:19,400 --> 00:10:22,200
Zhao Ming Yang, listen to me.

112
00:10:22,200 --> 00:10:25,700
You'd better not be hiding anything from me,

113
00:10:25,700 --> 00:10:29,200
or I'll teach you a lesson.

114
00:10:30,600 --> 00:10:33,500
Why would I dare hide anything from you?

115
00:10:34,400 --> 00:10:39,200
Aren't you like a little empress dowager?

116
00:10:40,600 --> 00:10:44,000
- What did you say?
- I said my sister is innocent, kind, smart, brave, and

117
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:45,900
best in the world.

118
00:10:47,400 --> 00:10:50,500
You're exaggerating the compliments.

119
00:10:50,500 --> 00:10:54,900
I'm just smart and incomparably beautiful.

120
00:10:59,700 --> 00:11:02,800
All right, I'm off to work.

121
00:11:02,800 --> 00:11:05,700
You'd better behave at home.

122
00:11:16,800 --> 00:11:18,500
Xin Ran!

123
00:11:34,600 --> 00:11:37,900
Xin… Xin Ran, I didn't…

124
00:11:37,900 --> 00:11:39,700
You…

125
00:11:41,200 --> 00:11:43,400
Xin Ran, I really didn't mean to.

126
00:11:43,400 --> 00:11:46,500
Let me explain! Forgive me!

127
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:52,000
Xin Ran! Xin Ran!

128
00:11:56,400 --> 00:11:59,000
Xin Ran! Xin Ran!

129
00:12:02,480 --> 00:12:05,650
<i>[President Gu Yi Chen]</i>

130
00:12:09,000 --> 00:12:12,600
President Gu, this is our new project's accounting sheet.

131
00:12:12,600 --> 00:12:14,400
Please review.

132
00:12:15,800 --> 00:12:18,800
Let's agree, you can't sign on my hand this time.

133
00:12:18,800 --> 00:12:20,200
You signed on my hand before,

134
00:12:20,200 --> 00:12:25,500
and the operations director looked at me like I was an alien.

135
00:12:25,500 --> 00:12:29,200
How about I sign on your forehead this time?

136
00:12:29,200 --> 00:12:31,100
Gu Yi Chen!

137
00:12:40,600 --> 00:12:42,700
Did you eat?

138
00:12:42,700 --> 00:12:44,600
Yes, I did.

139
00:12:44,600 --> 00:12:47,400
Breakfast? Lunch?

140
00:12:48,100 --> 00:12:51,100
Breakfast, lunch, hey!

141
00:12:51,100 --> 00:12:53,700
I'm discussing the project with you.

142
00:13:01,900 --> 00:13:03,500
Sit down.

143
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:11,000
Can you sign the accounting sheet first?

144
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:15,000
Read it to me.

145
00:13:20,400 --> 00:13:25,600
Operations cost and accounts for "Meeting You" project.

146
00:13:28,800 --> 00:13:31,800
Game feasibility analysis.

147
00:13:33,600 --> 00:13:35,400
I already had breakfast.

148
00:13:35,400 --> 00:13:37,100
Keep reading.

149
00:13:38,600 --> 00:13:43,400
Team estimates for project setup are as follows:

150
00:13:46,600 --> 00:13:49,100
concept artwork cost calculation,

151
00:13:49,800 --> 00:13:52,400
special effects modeling calculation,

152
00:14:00,800 --> 00:14:04,000
project analysis, operational advantages,

153
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:07,400
main program establishment calculation.

154
00:14:18,800 --> 00:14:20,700
Sweet milk again.

155
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:24,700
Is it sweet?

156
00:14:27,800 --> 00:14:31,700
♫ <i>I don't want to say who is at fault</i> ♫

157
00:14:31,700 --> 00:14:35,900
♫ <i>Who really understands me?</i> ♫

158
00:14:35,900 --> 00:14:39,400
♫ <i>Please forgive my persistence</i> ♫

159
00:14:39,400 --> 00:14:43,900
♫ <i>The almost-forgotten promise</i> ♫

160
00:14:43,900 --> 00:14:51,300
♫ <i>Is anything still worthy for me to watch over?</i> ♫

161
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:11,000
Assistant Sheng! I'm here to submit a report to President Gu.

162
00:15:11,000 --> 00:15:14,200
I finished reporting. I'm leaving now.

163
00:15:22,200 --> 00:15:24,000
Oh my gosh.

164
00:15:26,500 --> 00:15:28,600
The amount of PDA you two are showing…

165
00:15:28,600 --> 00:15:31,800
I'm so full, I don't even need lunch anymore. (PDA is known as "dog food.")

166
00:15:32,600 --> 00:15:34,200
Jealous?

167
00:15:34,200 --> 00:15:38,200
Jealous of your office romance?

168
00:15:38,200 --> 00:15:40,400
What should I be jealous?

169
00:15:41,600 --> 00:15:43,800
If you feel so frustrated, go date someone.

170
00:15:43,800 --> 00:15:45,400
I can dat—

171
00:15:46,400 --> 00:15:48,100
What did you say?

172
00:15:49,000 --> 00:15:52,200
Gu Yi Chen, I'm warning you.

173
00:15:52,200 --> 00:15:55,000
Even "single dogs" have their dignity.

174
00:15:55,800 --> 00:15:59,800
If you keep throwing your relationship in my face,

175
00:15:59,800 --> 00:16:02,100
be careful I don't quit.

176
00:16:10,000 --> 00:16:12,000
All right, let's talk business.

177
00:16:13,700 --> 00:16:16,000
I've finished reading your data analysis.

178
00:16:16,000 --> 00:16:20,300
But why is only Legend of the Mighty's data increasing

179
00:16:20,300 --> 00:16:23,400
and all other mobile games' data decreasing?

180
00:16:23,400 --> 00:16:25,000
You noticed that, too?

181
00:16:25,800 --> 00:16:28,500
I noticed it when I did the overall database analysis.

182
00:16:28,500 --> 00:16:31,200
Although our reach rate (views) increased this quarter,

183
00:16:31,200 --> 00:16:34,000
the overall business volume has decreased.

184
00:16:34,000 --> 00:16:37,800
While the rate of decline is only a fraction of a percent,

185
00:16:37,800 --> 00:16:41,800
the trend data is slightly decreasing.

186
00:16:41,800 --> 00:16:44,500
- Have you identified what's wrong?
- Not yet.

187
00:16:44,500 --> 00:16:50,200
We may have to re-calculate all mobile game projects in the company.

188
00:16:50,800 --> 00:16:53,400
What's the situation with UA and Hechuan?

189
00:16:53,400 --> 00:16:56,600
After Legend of the Mighty launched, we didn't hear much from them.

190
00:16:56,600 --> 00:17:00,600
During the Expo, I attended their project presentation meeting.

191
00:17:00,600 --> 00:17:05,000
The general feeling was they kept a low profile.

192
00:17:05,000 --> 00:17:09,300
You mean they've even reduced project promotions?

193
00:17:09,300 --> 00:17:12,400
In terms of quantity, yes.

194
00:17:12,400 --> 00:17:17,800
After UA and Hechuan merge their resources, they should be very formidable.

195
00:17:17,800 --> 00:17:21,200
Before UA came to China, they were very bold and aggressive.

196
00:17:21,200 --> 00:17:24,800
There is no reason to keep a low profile after teaming up with Hechuan.

197
00:17:24,800 --> 00:17:28,400
Actually, I've done much data analysis lately.

198
00:17:28,400 --> 00:17:32,000
Based on your analysis, it does seem strange.

199
00:17:32,000 --> 00:17:35,400
Could they be working on another project,

200
00:17:35,400 --> 00:17:37,700
planning to catch us off guard?

201
00:17:38,640 --> 00:17:42,840
No news from UA and Hechuan means we should beware.

202
00:17:42,840 --> 00:17:44,960
Qiao Nan, I'll leave the rest to you.

203
00:17:44,960 --> 00:17:47,880
- Investigate them fully.
- Okay.

204
00:17:47,880 --> 00:17:51,080
There's a top-level industry meeting this afternoon.

205
00:17:51,080 --> 00:17:52,728
I'll go.

206
00:17:53,900 --> 00:17:55,800
I will go.

207
00:17:55,800 --> 00:17:58,620
You? You're going personally?

208
00:17:58,620 --> 00:18:01,420
Recently, you've worked hard on big data analysis.

209
00:18:01,420 --> 00:18:05,960
Let me go this time. I can look at the industry and what's happening at Hechuan.

210
00:18:05,960 --> 00:18:08,860
But this is a meeting hosted by the industry association.

211
00:18:08,860 --> 00:18:12,480
Top executives from major companies and media representatives will be present.

212
00:18:12,480 --> 00:18:14,880
I can't help you manage relationships. I fear if you go alone…

213
00:18:14,880 --> 00:18:17,320
It's all right. Someone said,

214
00:18:17,320 --> 00:18:20,900
she hoped I could slowly open my heart and return to the crowd.

215
00:18:20,900 --> 00:18:25,820
Perhaps now is the best time to start.

216
00:18:36,480 --> 00:18:39,680
<i>[This afternoon I attend a meeting. Don't wait for my return.]</i>

217
00:18:40,420 --> 00:18:41,920
<i>[Okay.]</i>

218
00:18:41,920 --> 00:18:43,360
<i>[Remember to have dinner.]</i>

219
00:18:43,360 --> 00:18:45,760
<i>[If you don't have time, go to my office.]</i>

220
00:18:45,760 --> 00:18:48,360
<i>[The cake and milk are in the tea cabinet.]</i>

221
00:18:49,120 --> 00:18:50,600
<i>[I got it.]</i>

222
00:18:50,600 --> 00:18:52,540
<i>[Are you annoyed with my clinginess again?]</i>

223
00:18:53,260 --> 00:18:54,950
<i>[Meow]</i>

224
00:19:00,300 --> 00:19:01,812
Group Leader.

225
00:19:02,740 --> 00:19:04,340
Why are you back?

226
00:19:04,340 --> 00:19:06,360
Isn't there a group meeting at the program center today?

227
00:19:06,360 --> 00:19:07,440
This was already done.

228
00:19:07,440 --> 00:19:10,860
Today, the center did some testing on our new phase program,

229
00:19:10,860 --> 00:19:12,520
and teachers found a few bugs.

230
00:19:12,520 --> 00:19:15,120
We may need to re-test once repairs are made.

231
00:19:15,120 --> 00:19:17,040
Please take a look, Group Leader.

232
00:19:36,300 --> 00:19:37,640
Driver, start the car.

233
00:19:37,640 --> 00:19:39,500
Fang Mi?

234
00:19:39,500 --> 00:19:41,500
Isn't this a ride-sharing car?

235
00:19:41,500 --> 00:19:44,360
Driver, I want to share a ride.

236
00:19:44,360 --> 00:19:46,700
Come on. I've been working overtime for a week.

237
00:19:46,700 --> 00:19:48,440
I can finally go home early today.

238
00:19:48,440 --> 00:19:51,000
Can you let me go home and rest?

239
00:19:51,000 --> 00:19:55,920
Senior Nan, you've really lost weight.

240
00:19:55,920 --> 00:19:59,500
You need the power of love to recharge.

241
00:19:59,500 --> 00:20:01,660
Fang Mi.

242
00:20:01,660 --> 00:20:05,080
I've found the taste of happiness.

243
00:20:05,080 --> 00:20:07,480
Don't you want to try it with me?

244
00:20:17,696 --> 00:20:19,828
<i>[The Taste of Happiness]</i>

245
00:20:32,800 --> 00:20:37,180
Senior Nan, what are you thinking? Let's get out.

246
00:20:37,180 --> 00:20:38,832
Okay.

247
00:20:54,994 --> 00:20:57,393
<i>[Tong Coffee Since 2020]</i>

248
00:21:06,560 --> 00:21:08,360
Senior Nan,

249
00:21:08,360 --> 00:21:11,380
don't underestimate this porridge bowl. It may seem ordinary,

250
00:21:11,380 --> 00:21:15,720
but after I came back to China, it's the warmest, tastiest

251
00:21:15,720 --> 00:21:18,120
and most comforting food I've eaten.

252
00:21:19,140 --> 00:21:21,240
- Is it really that amazing?
